src: tɕʰeme nɯra tʰɯ-sta-nɯ

trs: I will give you my daughter.'  (28-smAnmi, 267)

trs: The smallest one is very nice as a person.' (31-deluge, 124)

trs: Your elder sister was like that, she had me killed (while I was a) bird, and had also me killed (while I was a) thorn.' (2005 Kunbzang, 403-404)

src: rgɤtpu nɯ ɣɯ ɯ-kɯ-rtoʁ jo-ɣi.

src: kʰɤxtɤndo tɕu ko-zo

trs: I went to Tshobdun to teach. There, I had a hen again.' (150819 kumpGa, 78-79)

trs: He was on the east side.' (28-qAjdoskAt, 152)

trs: One day, (the bear finally) met (the rabbit).' (2011-13-qala, 22)

src: tɕe ɯ-xtɤpa cʰo ɯ-mi, ɯ-jaʁ, ɯ-ŋgɯ-cʰu nɯra ɲɯ-wɣrum.
trs: The lower part of its body, its feet, its paws, the inside part are white.' (20-xsar, 23)

trs: (The crossoptilon) would take (the weasel) from the mountain here to the mountain over there (on the other side of the river).' (23-qapGAmtWmtW, 88)

src: qartsɯ tɕe ɲɯ-jpum ftɕar tɕe tu-mbro ŋu.

trs: In my opinion, (since) they have horns, (they should be able to fight the predators off).' (20-RmbroN, 64)

src: tɕe ɯʑo ɯ-sɯm tɕe tɕe tu-tsɯm tɕe tɕendɤre iʑora ji-sɤtɕʰa ra lonba ʑo tɯ-ci ɲɯ-sɯ-ɤβze to-ʁmɯɣ.

src: [kʰu chondɤre] mbro ni to-rɤkrɤz-ndʑi.
trs: The tiger and the horse had a discussion.' (20-tArka, 32)

src: tɕe ɯ-rqʰu nɯ ɣɯrni laʁma ɯ-ŋgɯ nɯ [sɤjku cʰo] ɲɯ-naχtɕɯɣ-ndʑi ri
trs: Apart from the fact that its bark is red, it is identical in the inside with the birch.' (06-mbrAj, 13)

src: tɕeri ɯʑo ndɤre, qajdo cʰo ra kɯ ndɤ tú-wɣ-ndza ɕti
trs: But it is eaten by crows and other (animals).' (26-NalitCaRmbWm, 140)

src: [ɯ-pɯ ra cʰo] tɯtɯrca to-ndza-nɯ tɕe to-nɯ-ʑɣɤ-ɕɯ-fka-nɯ ʑo ɲɯ-ŋu.
trs: (The eagle) ate them together with its fledglings and they ate to their full.' (huli yu shanying-zh, 28)

src: tɕe ɯ-rʑaβ cʰo ndʑi-me ci tu tɕe,
trs: He and his wife have a daughter.' (14-siblings, 313)

src: tɤ-rpi nɤ tɤ-rpi ʑo ɲɯ-sɯ-βzu-nɯ ɲɯ-ŋu tɕe,
trs: They ask (lamas) to chant sutras after sutras.' (2003kandZislama, 112)

src: tɕe ɯ-χti nɯ kɯ cʰa ntsɯ ku-tsʰi pɯ-ŋu tɕe cʰa nɤ cʰa ku-tsʰi pjɯ-ɕti tɕe
trs: Her husband used to drink all the time, drank alcohol again and again.' (17-lhazgron, 64)

src: tɯ-ci nɯ taʁ nɤ taʁ, taʁ nɤ taʁ tu-ɣi pjɤ-ɕti
trs: The water was raising up and up.' (31-deluge, 19)

src: tʂu nɤ tʂu pjɤ-ɕe qʰe,
trs: He went all the way down.' (140511 alading-zhn 105)

src: qandʑɣi sɤznɤ ɲɯ-wxti, qaliaʁ sɤznɤ ɲɯ-xtɕi
trs: It is bigger than a falcon, and smaller than an eagle.' (2011-08-kuwu, 40-41)

src: ɯʑo nɯ aʑo sɤz tɯ-xpa wxti
trs: She is one year older than me.' (12-BzaNsa, 94)

src: nɤ-mu kɤ-fsraŋ mɤ-tɯ-cʰa tɕe, nɯ sɤznɤ, a-rca jɤ-ɣi tɕe, a-rca, nɤki, laχɕi pɯ-βzjoz
trs: You cannot save your mother, rather than that, come with me to learn  some abilities.' (150826 baoliandeng-zh, 142-143)

src: ki kɤ-rtsi kɯ-tu me nɤ, aʑo nɯ sɤznɤ, nɤkinɯ, kʰa kɯ-qanɯ\redp{}nɯ ɯ-ŋgɯ zɯ, nɤkinɯ, tɯ-ɕpɤβ kɯβde-rzɯɣ tɤ-kɤ-lɤt nɯnɯ ku-sɤlɤɣi-a cʰa-a ɕti nɤ!
trs: (What you ask) is nothing, I am even able to put together a corpse that had been cut into four pieces in a dark house.'  (140512 alibaba-zh, 170)

src: kɯki sɤlaŋpʰɤn ki nɯ sɤznɤ ɲɯ-wxti wo tɕe kʰa ju-nɯ-tsɯm-a tɕe,
trs: This basin is really big, I will take it home.' (150831 jubaopen, 22)

src: tɤ-pɤtso kɯ-ɣɤwu ʑo kɤ-nɯɕpɯz mɤ-spe-a ma nɯ mɯma spe-a
trs: I cannot imitate a baby crying, but apart form that I can imitate (all animal sounds).' (27-kikakCi, 143)

src: kɤ-sɤŋo ʁɟa qʰe,  nɯ-mtɕʰi kɤ-χpjɤt ʁɟa kɯ kú-wɣ-spa ɕti.  nɯ mɤɕtʂa mɤ-kʰɯ.
trs: (In order to learn the Tshobdun language, since it has no writing system), one has no choice but to listen and observe people's mouth to learn it, otherwise it is not possible.' (150901 tshuBdWnskAt, 41-44)

src: tɯrme tɯ-fsu ɕaŋtaʁ tu-mbro mɤ-cʰa.
trs: It cannot grow higher than a person.'(11-qarGW, 29)

src: kɯmŋɤsqɤ-rʑaʁ ɕaŋtaʁ cʰɯ-mdɯ-nɯ mɤ-ŋgrɤl tu-ti-nɯ ɲɯ-ŋu.
trs: They cannot live more than fifty days, it is said.' (26-GZo, 41)

src: ɯ-pɯ nɯnɯ χsɯm ɕaŋtaʁ tu mɯ́j-ŋgrɤl
trs: It does not usually have more than three offsprings.' (2011-08-kuwu, 14)

src: iʑora kɯ, nɤki, tsʰuβdɯn ɕaŋlo nɯra `stɤtpa-pɯ' tu-ti-j ŋu.
trs: We call the people (who live) in Tshobdun and further upstream `Stotpa'.' (23-tCAphW, 14)

imt: \textsc{3sg}.\textsc{poss}-normal walnut  \textsc{dem} \textsc{lnk} fifteen-year until \textsc{3sg}.\textsc{poss}-fruit \textsc{ipfv}-attach \textsc{neg}:\textsc{sens}-can \textsc{aor}-\textsc{inv}-plant just.after \textsc{3sg}.\textsc{poss}-seed \textsc{ipfv}-\textsc{inv}-plant \textsc{3sg}.\textsc{poss}-after fifteen-year only.after \textsc{lnk} \textsc{3sg}.\textsc{poss}-fruit \textsc{ipfv}-attach be:\textsc{fact} \textsc{ipfv}-say-\textsc{pl} be.usually.the.case:\textsc{fact} \textsc{lnk}
src: ɯ-xso ʑɴɢɯloʁ nɯnɯ, tɕe sqamŋu-xpa mɤɕtʂa ɯ-mat ku-tsʰoʁ mɯ́j-cʰa. pɯ́-wɣ-ji ɕimɯma, ɯ-rɣi pjɯ́-wɣ-ji ɯ-qʰu,  sqamŋu-xpa kóʁmɯz nɤ ɯ-mat ku-tsʰoʁ ŋu tu-ti-nɯ ŋgrɤl tɕe,
trs: Usually, the walnut tree cannot have walnuts until fifteen years (have passed). Just after one has planted it, after one plants its seeds, it is only fifteen years later that it bears nuts, they say.' (12-ndZiNgri, 166-167)

src: tɕe tɤ-mu nɯ, nɯ ɯ-qʰu ɕaŋpɕi ʑo kɤ-rɯndzɤqʰɤjɯ ta-znɯna
trs: From that (time) on, the mother stopped to eat on her own without sharing.' (tWJo 2005, 53)

src: tɕe ɯ-ŋgu jɤznɤ tɕe, ɯ-mɤlɤjaʁ nɯra mɯ-cʰɯ-pʰaʁ-nɯ tɕe,  tɕe nɯ ɣɯ ɯ-ndʐi kɯ-fsɯ\redp{}fse nɯ pjɯ-qaʁ-nɯ tɕe tɕe
trs: In the beginning, they don't cut off the limbs (from the cattle's body), and take out the skin (in such a way as to preserve its shape) exactly like (that of the living animal).' (06-BGa, 94)

src: jɯfɕɯr <gongxun> a-ɕki jɤ-ɣe.
trs: Yesterday Gong Xun came to (see) me.' (160320, conversation)

src: tɕe smɤt tɯmda rɟɤlpu ɣɯ ɯ-ɕki nɯtɕu, nɤkinɯ, ɯ-rʑaβ ɯ-kɯ-tʰu cʰɤ-ɕe tɕe,
trs: He went to ask the king of the lower valley for (one his daughter to take as) a wife.' (2014-kWlAG, 16)

src: tɕe tɤ-tɕɯ nɯ kɯ ɯ-wa ɯ-pʰe nɯra pɯ-kɯ-fse nɯra to-ti ɲɯ-ŋu
trs: The boy told his father the things that had happened.' (qachGa2012, 175)

src: nɤʑo ɯ-mɤ-ɲɯ-tɯ-stu nɤ, ʑara nɯ-ɕki tɤ-tʰe jɤɣ
trs: If you don't believe it, ask them!' (140508 shier ge tiaowu de gongzhu-zh, 190)

src: nɯ tɤ-pɤtso nɯ ɯ-ɕki to-rɯɕmi.
trs: It spoke to the child.' (150831 renshen wawa-zh, 36)

src: ɯ-nmaʁ ɯ-ɕki ɲɤ-kʰo tɕe,
trs: She gave it to her husband.' (qajdoskAt, 71)

src: tɕe tɤŋe nɯ nɯɣ-me tɕe, tɕe tɤŋe ɯ-ɕki ʁɟa ʑo ɕ-tu-ru tɕe, tɯʑo tɯ-ɕki maka ʑo mɤ-ru
trs: (If the yeti catches you), it is afraid of the sun, it looks at the sun the whole time, and does not look at you.' (140510 mYWrgAt, 13)

src: ɯ-rte nɯ ɯ-rna ɯ-ɕki pɯ-kɯ-ɴqoʁ nɯnɯ pjɤ-mɟa tɕe ɯ-ku ɯ-taʁ to-ta.
trs: He took the hat that was hanging on his ear and put it on his head.' (140505 liuhaohan zoubian tianxia-zh, 164)

src: tɤŋe cʰo slɤŋe ʑŋgri ra nɯ-pʰe nɯtɕu kɤ-nɤɕqa a-pɯ-tɯ-cʰa ra ma,
trs: (When you are) by the sun, the moon and the stars, you will have to bear (the heat and the cold), otherwise...' (2003kandZislama, 53)

src: li tɕetu tɤ-ɣe qʰe, ɯ-wa ɯ-ɕki ku-nɯ-rɤʑi, tɕeki pɯ-ari qʰe, ɯ-wɯ ɯ-wi ni ndʑi-ɕki ju-nɯ-ɕe qʰe,
trs: When she comes up there, she stays at her father's house, and when she goes down there, she goes to her grandparent's place.' (14-siblings, 305)

src: aʑo kɯnɤ nɤ-rca ɣi-a ɕti
trs: I am coming/going with you.' (2011-05-nyima, 171)

src: nɯʑora ɣɯ nɯ-tɤ-sno kɯ-fse ɯ-tsʰɤt nɯ, tɕiʑo ɣɯ, tɕi-xɕɤndʑu χsɯ-ldʑa pɯ-tu tɕe, nɯnɯ lɤ-nɯ-βlɯ-tɕi ɕti wo
trs: Instead of a saddle like yours, we had three twigs, this is what we burned.' (Kunbzang 2003, 203)

src: aʑo nɤ-tsʰɤt, nɤki, si nɯ tu-ɣɯjtsi-a jɤɣ
trs: I can support the tree for you/instead of you (while you fetch it).' (150830 afanti-zh, 136)

src: si maŋe tɕe tɕe nɯnɯtɕu tɕe, nɯ-si ɯ-tsʰɤt ɲɯ-ŋu
trs: (since) there are no trees, (dung) is used there to replace the firewood.' (05-tamar, 10-11)

src: nɯ tɤ-nɯ-ndɤm tɕe aʑo a-tsʰɤt ŋu tɕe
trs: Take these instead of me (as a compensation).' (2003kAndzwsqhaj2, 141)

src: rkaŋraŋ ɯ-tsʰɤt tsa ɲɯ-kɯ-nɤɕtʂaʁli-a-nɯ raʁmaʁ ma
trs: Rkangrang, don't go over the top in your torturing of me (torture me with proper measure), please? (Norbzang 2005, 245)

src: ɯ-tsʰɤt tu-sɯ-βzu-nɯ mɯ́j-kʰɯ ma, nɯ-kɤ-kʰo nɯ mɯ-tʰa-ɕkɯt mɤɕtʂa tu-ndze ɲɯ-ɕti.
trs: They cannot make (the monkey eat) with measure, as it continues eating the (food) that is given to it until there is none.' (19-GzW, 60)

imt: \textsc{lnk} \textsc{dem} \textsc{3sg}.\textsc{poss}-proper.measure \textsc{dem}  \textsc{3sg}.\textsc{poss}-young once once two exist:\textsc{fact} once once one-piece apart.from not.exist:\textsc{fact} \textsc{lnk} for.this.reason \textsc{sens}-be
src: tɕe nɯnɯ ɯ-tsʰɤt nɯnɯ ɯ-pɯ ci ci ʁnɯz tu, ci ci tɯ-rdoʁ ma me tɕe núndʐa ɲɯ-ŋu.
trs: This is why, depending on the circumstances, sometimes (the goat) has two kids, sometimes only one.' (05-qaZo, 28)

src: ɯ-taʁ zɯ kɤ-amdzɯ nɤ tɤ-lu pa-tɕɤt ɲɯ-ŋu
trs: She sat on him and milked.' (2005 Kunbzang, 81)

src: tɕendɤre nɯnɯ kʰɯtsa ɯ-mŋu jamar kɯ-wxti tu,
trs: Some are about as big as the mouth of a bowl.' (22-BlamajmAG, 130)

src: tɕendre pɣɤtɕɯ nɯ mtsʰu ɯ-mŋu nɯtɕu `ʂɯt' to-ti to-nɯ-ɬoʁ.
trs: The bird came out of the shore of the lake with a noise.' (2014-kWlAG, 556)

src: mtsʰu ɯ-qa zɯ nɤrwɯ mɤ-kɯ-naχtɕɯɣ ci ɣɤʑu tɕe,
trs: At the bottom of the sea, there is a jewel unlike any other.' (2012 Kunbzang, 12)

src: ɯ-ndo tɕe maka kɯ-tu ɲɯ-me ɲɯ-ŋu tɕe,
trs: In the end, nothing is left.' (04-xiaocunzhuang-zh, 63)

src: tɕe nɯ ɯ-ndʐi nɯnɯ pjɯ-χtsɤβ-nɯ tɕe tɕe tɯ-ŋga ɯ-ndo ri ku-lɤt-nɯ, tɯ-ŋga ɯ-kuŋa, ɯ-pɤloʁ ɯ-ku, ɯ-ndo nɯra ku-lɤt-nɯ,  tu-sɯ-fskɤr-nɯ ŋu.
trs: They tan its hide (of the otter) and put it on the lower opening of the clothes, on the collar of clothes, the cuffs of the sleeves and the lower opening, and make it around (these openings).' (28-qapar, 96)

src: qaʑmbri nɯ, tɯ-ji ɯ-ndo, tɯ-ji ɯ-mŋu nɯra aʁɤndɯndɤt ʑo tu-ɬoʁ ɕti
trs: The vine, it grows everywhere, on both sides of the fields.' (06-qaZmbri, 12)

src: tʂʰa tɤ́-wɣ-rku tɕe kʰɯtsa ɯ-mŋuɕɯmŋu stʰɯci tu-zɣɯt mɤ-ra ma kɤ-ndo tɕe sɤ-ɕke
trs: When one pours tea, it should not reach the limit of the mouth of the bowl, otherwise it will be burning when one holds it.' (elicited)

src: tɕe pʰaʁrgot ri li ɯʑo ɯ-stu ʑo ɲɤ-ɣi qʰe,  ɕɤmɯɣdɯ kɤ-lɤt mɯ-pjɤ-nɤz qʰe pʰaʁrgot jo-nɯ-ɕe.
trs: The boar came directly at him, but he did not dare to shoot and the boar went away.' (150829 phaRrgot, 8)

src: tɕe ɯ-ku kɯ-ɤmtɕoʁ ɲɯ-ŋu tɕe, tɯ-taʁ ku-otsa tɕe ɲɯ-ɕɯ-mŋɤm.
trs: (The fir needles) are pointy-headed, they prick people, it hurts.'  (08-tWrgi, 27)

src: tɯrmɯkʰa tɕe tɯlɤt nɯ ɯ-taʁ ko-ɴqoʁ tɕe
trs: In the evening, he grabbed the second sister.' (07-deluge, 47)

src: maka ʑo ɯ-taʁ mɯ-pjɤ-pe-ndʑi qhe, pjɤ-ŋɤn-ndʑi
trs: They did not treat him well, they treated him badly. (2014-kWlAG, 114)

src: a-pi ra a-taʁ nɯ-tɯ-pe pɯ-sɤre ʑo tɕe
trs: My elder brothers treated me very well.' (140501 tshering skyid, 46)

src: nɤ-taʁ stu-a mbat-a ʑo ɕti
trs: I will treat you well.' (2005lobzang, 33)

src: ɯ-taʁ tɯ-mci pjɯ́-wɣ-lɤt
trs: If one spits on it,' (08-qaJAGi, 27)

imt: servant \textsc{pl} \textsc{3pl}.\textsc{poss}-on also \textsc{aor}:\textsc{east}-go[II] \textsc{lnk} ladle-back once \textsc{ipfv}-release \textsc{aor}:\textsc{west}-come[II] \textsc{lnk} fist once \textsc{ipfv}-release
src: ʁjoʁ ra nɯ-taʁ kɯnɤ kɤ-ari tɕe scoʁ-qʰu ci tu-lɤt, nɯ-ɣe tɕe tɤŋkʰɯt ci tu-lɤt
trs: Every time she went right she would hit the servants with the back of the ladle, every time she went left she hit them with the fist.' (2002 qaCpa, 143)

src: ʑmbrɯ ɯ-taʁ to-ɕe tɕe jo-nɯ-ɕe
trs: He took a boat and went back home.' (150907 niexiaoqian-zh, 140)

src: ʑmbrɯ ɯ-taʁ pjɤ-ɬoʁ-nɯ
trs: They took off the boats.' (140508 shier ge tiaowu de gongzhu-zh, 149)

src: tɕe jɯɣi ɯ-taʁ tu-fɕɤt tɕe,
trs: It is told in a book, that...' (27-qaCpa, 5)

src: khɯtsa ɯ-ŋgɯ tɯ-ci tu-rku-nɯ tɕe,
trs: People used to put water in a bowl, and...' (29-mWBZi, 129)

src: tɯ-ji ɯ-ŋgɯ zɯ tsʰɤt ɯ-ɣli nɯ cʰɯ́-wɣ-lɤt tɕe, tɤ-rɤku wuma ʑo tu-sɤpe cʰa
trs: If one spreads goat manure on the fields, it can make the crops grow really well.' (05-qaZo, 33)

src: <chuzu> ɯ-ŋgɯ tʰɯ-ɣe-a tɕe
trs: I came on a taxi.' (2010-01-Dpalcan, 28)

imt: \textsc{3sg}.\textsc{poss}-downstream downstream water.trough \textsc{dem} \textsc{erg} \textsc{filler} mill \textsc{3sg}.\textsc{poss}-under \textsc{loc} water.wheel exist:\textsc{fact} \textsc{lnk} water.wheel \textsc{3sg}.\textsc{poss}-on \textsc{loc} \textsc{ipfv}:\textsc{downstream}-release \textsc{lnk} \textsc{lnk} water.wheel \textsc{dem}:\textsc{loc} \textsc{loc} blades \textsc{obj}:\textsc{pcp}-say exist:\textsc{fact} \textsc{lnk}
src: ɯ-tʰɤcu maŋtʰi qʰajŋgɯ nɯ kɯ, nɤki, βɣa ɯ-pa ri tɕʰɯŋkʰɤr tu tɕe, tɕʰɯŋkʰɤr ɯ-taʁ ri cʰɯ-lɤt tɕe, tɕʰɯŋkʰɤr ɯ-taʁ nɯre ri βɣɤrnɤjwaʁ kɤ-ti tu tɕe
trs: The inferior water trough -- under the mill there is a water wheel -- (the water trough) directs (the water) onto that water wheel -- on the water wheel there are things called `blades'.' (06-BGa, 27-31)

src: ɯ-tʰoʁ ɯ-pa ri tu-ɬoʁ nɯra mɯ́j-cʰa
trs: (Its shoots) cannot come out from under the ground.'  (15-babW, 45)

src: χsɤr kʰri ɯ-taʁ zɯ pjɤ-rɤʑi tɕe ɯ-tɯ-ɣɤχsrɯ pjɤ-saχaʁ ʑo.
trs: He was sitting on the golden bed, very handsome.' (2014-kWlAG, 409)

src: rɟɤmtsʰu ɣɯ ɯ-rkɯ qambɯt ɯ-taʁ nɯtɕu pjɤ-rɤʑi.
trs: He stayed on the beach.' (140511 xinbada-zh, 167)

src: nɯ ɯ-mdoʁ nɯ aj kɤ-ti mɯ́j-spe-a ma arŋi ɯ-ŋgɯz kɯnɤ pɣi kɯ-fse
trs: I cannot say its colour, it is somewhere between green and grey.' (06-qaZmbri, 56)

src: χɕitka ɯ-raŋ tɕe, tɕendɤre pɣa ra, nɯ-kɤ-ndza maka cʰɯ-me ɲɯ-ŋu tɕe, tɕendɤre ɯ-tɯ-mtsɯr pjɤ-saχaʁ ʑo ɲɯ-ŋu,
trs: In spring, the birds' food has gone out and (that crow) was extremely hungry.' (kWjujmAlu, 6)

src: ɯ-rɤɣ ɣɤʑu ma nɤkinɯ sɲikuku ʑo ɲɯ-maʁ
trs: (The rut) occurs at a specific time, not every day.' (27-qartshAz, 155)

src: tɕendɤre ɯ-fsaqʰe tɕe nɯ ɯ-rɤɣ tɕe li lo-ɣi
trs: It came back at exactly the same time the next year.' (22-qomndroN, 46)

src: ci ɯ-mpʰru ci ʑo ko-nɯpoʁ qʰe lo-sɯ-ɣe.
trs: (The mother) kissed (her children) one after the one and had them come (inside the house).' (160701 poucet2, 38)

src: tɕe nɯ ɯ-mpʰru tɕe tɕʰi to-ti?
trs: What does it say next?' (140522 Kamnyu zgo)

src: tɕe tɯ-rdoʁ pjɤ-sat tɕe tɕeri nɯnɯ ɯ-mpʰru tɯ-sla jamar nɯnɯ tɯ-ci ɯ-taʁ nɯtɕu ɯ-zda nɯ lo-ɕe nɤ cʰɤ-ɣi, lo-ɕe nɤ cʰɤ-ɣi ɲɤ-ɕar
trs: (Someone) killed one of them, and after that, (the other one) flew along the river searching for its mate for about one month.' (22-qomndroN, 44)

src: aʑo ku-ɕe-a tɕe z-ɲɯ-saʁjar-a ŋu tɕe nɯ ɯ-pɤrtʰɤβ tɕe nɯʑo ra kɯ ɕ-pɯ-rla-nɯ je tɕe lɤ-tsɯm-nɯ je
trs: I will go there and delay him$_i$, and in the meantime, you go there and untie him$_j$, and take him$_j$ away.' (tWJo 2005, 37)

src: nɤki tɤtʂu nɯ a-jaʁ tɤ-kʰɤm!
trs: Hand over to me (up here) that lamp.' (140511 alading-zh, 122)

src: kɯki mbro ki nɤ-jaʁ ɲɯ-kʰo-j ŋu
trs: (If you succeed), we will give you this horse.'  (X1-qachGa, 62)

src: iɕqʰa tɤtʂu nɯ a-jaʁ a-nɯ-zɣɯt ra
trs: I have to obtain this lamp.' (140511 alading-zh, 212)

src: tɕʰi ra na-sɯso ʑo nɯ, ɯ-jaʁ ju-nɯ-sɯ-ɤzɣɯt pjɤ-cʰa.
trs: He was able to get whatever he wanted.' (140508 benling gaoqiang de si xiongdi-zh, 47)

src: jinde tɕe ɯ-kɯ-sat koŋla maŋe tɕe, nɯ qarma ɯ-muj kɯnɤ tɯ-jaʁ mɯ́j-ɣi wo
trs: Nowadays nobody kills crossoptilons, one cannot even get their feathers (to use as ornaments).' (23-qapGAmtWmtW, 170)

src: pʰa kɤmɲɯ ɣɯ kɯ-pe ɣɯ ɯ-skɤt nɯtɕu to-βzu-nɯ ɲɯ-ŋu.
trs: People built it there for the benefit of all of Kamyu.' (150904 tshAcim, 32)

src: pɯ-cʰa-a nɯra nɤj nɤ-tʰɯrʑi kɯ pɯ-cʰa-a
trs: I succeeded all thanks to you.' (2011 04-smanmi, 112)

src: ma jinde nɯra kɯ-fse kɤ-mtsʰɤm maŋe tɕe, smɤn ɯ-tʰɯrʑi ɯmɤ-ŋu ma
trs: Nowadays we do not hear about (this disease), probably thanks to the medicine.' (27-tWfCAl, 52)
